org.getspout.spoutapi.player
Interface SpoutPlayer

All Superinterfaces:
org.bukkit.entity.AnimalTamer, org.bukkit.command.CommandSender, org.bukkit.configuration.serialization.ConfigurationSerializable, org.bukkit.entity.Entity, org.bukkit.entity.HumanEntity, org.bukkit.entity.LivingEntity, org.bukkit.OfflinePlayer, org.bukkit.permissions.Permissible, org.bukkit.entity.Player, org.bukkit.permissions.ServerOperator
public interface SpoutPlayer
extends org.bukkit.entity.Player

Represents a SpoutPlayer, which extends the standard Bukkit Player. SpoutPlayer's can be retrieved by casting Bukkit's org.bukkit.entity.Player class

                            org.bukkit.Location location)
Opens an inventory dialog to the player, with the given inventory displayed in the upper pane, and the player's inventory in the lower pane. The location is not used, but is passed to other plugins when notifying them of the open window

Parameters:
inventory - to use in the dialog GUI
location - that represents this inventory in the world (e.g Chest, Furnace). Use null if there is no physical location.

true if an inventory window was opened

                            org.bukkit.Location location,
                            boolean ignoreDistance)
Opens an inventory dialog to the player, with the given inventory displayed in the upper pane, and the player's inventory in the lower pane. The location is not used, but is passed to other plugins when notifying them of the open window

Parameters:
inventory - to use in the dialog GUI
location - that represents this inventory in the world (e.g Chest, Furnace). Use null if there is no physical location.

true if an inventory window was opened

setGravityMultiplier

@ClientOnly
void setGravityMultiplier(double multiplier)
Modifies the effects of gravity on the player's y axis movement. Ex: setGravityMultiplier(10) will cause players to fall ten times faster than normal. Warning, large modifiers may trigger fly-hack warnings. Default gravity multiplier is 1

Parameters:
multiplier - to set.

reconnect

@ClientOnly
void reconnect(String message,
                          String hostname,
                          int port)
Orders the client to reconnect to another server This method is also supported by some server to server teleporting mods. Players without the client mod will be given a kick message instructing them to join the other server

Parameters:
message - the message to include in the kick message for vanilla clients
hostname - the hostname of the other server
port - the port of the other server
